reviews.text:
Three of us came here for food and a few drinks on a Saturday night before heading elsewhere. The place wasn’t busy when two of us arrived (just us and another couple with their dog) but it obviously picked up not long after. Still, it certainly wasn’t hectic when we made our food order. The vibe of the place is really laid-back and the happy hour - with a very solid selection of beers - goes until 9pm, which is great.

Unfortunately I couldn’t say the same for the general service or the food. 

We ordered three mozzarella and portobello mushroom burgers and two portions of fries. We asked for a Cucumber Cooler cocktail shortly after for my girlfriend who arrived late. 

The first two burgers took more than 30 minutes to arrive. About 10 minutes later the first portion of fries arrived with the third burger (the first two burgers were well-eaten by this point and myself and my friend started tucking in to the fries, leaving my girlfriend to eat her burger separately while picking at the side order and wondering where her drink was).

Between 5-10 minutes later, the second lot of fries and the cocktail arrived. It didn’t take long for all food to be finished and beers to be drank. That left my girlfriend feeling rushed to finish a cocktail she’d been hoping to enjoy 15 minutes earlier.

There was no apology for this slow service. Just two separate assertions that the cocktail was on its way. 

Considering the bill reached nearly $800, including the ~$70 service charge, we expected better. 

We’d recommend the truffle sauce if you decide to get the fries, but the burgers (with a $98 price tag) were forgettable.
Good 'neighborhood bar' with a wide selection of beer, bar snacks and a pool table

Awesome local gem of a place. A very broad selection of can and bottle craft beer, and great value burgers and snack food. Staff are super helpful and friendly - will do their best to help you find the perfect beer if you ask.
I would give zero stars if possible. Food was a disaster...

Good beers and burgers, and you can play pool and darts while watching the harbor. Service really nice with smiling people.
And happy hour every day before 9pm !!!
